Bifurcated memory compliance system is fully designed and implemented.

## Acceptance Criteria Status

✅ Memory tagging schema — YAML frontmatter with `compliance_required: true`, two-directory structure
✅ Read enforcement — cloud sessions get `compliance_filter=cloud` by default; memory-compliant/ is never auto-injected by OpenClaw core
✅ Write classification — memory-scanner.ts indexes all files, anomaly detection flags misplaced files; prompt-build hook injects compliant memories only for compliance-mode sessions
✅ Architecture doc — docs/decisions/ADR-bifurcated-memory-compliance.md

## Key Components

- `src/util/compliance-model.ts` — isLocalModel / isCloudModel / isComplianceModel
- `src/util/memory-frontmatter.ts` — YAML frontmatter parser
- `src/services/memory-scanner.ts` — background indexer + anomaly detection
- `src/hooks/prompt-build.ts` — compliance memory injection gate
- `src/api/memories-fs.ts` — compliance_filter param + /compliance-summary + /anomalies
- `memory_compliance_index` DB table — tracks all memory files with compliance status

